result.name: PMQ

reviews.text: Loved the PMQ. Lots of arty designers curating their own styles and many you can watch in action.  Found some lovely quirky pieces no one will have back in Sydney including designer Mountain Yam. So glad i happened upon this place.

A good platform to allow local artisans & designers to show their works & wares.
Also a good way to preserve & make good use of a building with a rich colonial past

A former police headquarters and living quarters, PMQ is a revived marketplace for local designers and boutiques. This place is tailor-made for design lovers and offered for  hip public who'd love to escape from the hustling and bustling side of the city. A few restaurants are also found here like Taiwanese Cafe, Chinese fusion restaurant, etc. Curated exhibitions are organized periodically for art lovers.
Lovely place to visit.  Many fun and arty workshops, and nice things to buy.

If you love to shop museum design stores, you will love this place! There are 5 floors and 2 sections. 
The building used to be a school, then a police dormitory, it s a heritage building turned into a hipster shopping compound. 
My favourite store there is Matter Matters, Pomch.

reviews.text: 60多年歷史建築注入新的文創力量⋯
活化的脫變中👍👍👍
冬菇頭😎

Loved the PMQ. Lots of arty designers curating their own styles and many you can watch in action.  Found some lovely quirky pieces no one will have back in Sydney including designer Mountain Yam. So glad i happened upon this place.

這個PMQ元創坊是一個文青聚集地~
在鴨巴甸街一直行上去就會到達這裡的

前身是警察宿舍 將舊有建築物活化近年有很多
這裡是一個創意中心 亦是香港三級歷史建築
而這個地方挻好逛的 有很多不同的小商鋪

裡面有很多不同的藝術區/餐飲/活動舉行
而在地下大堂就有小活動 分為兩個活動🤔
而地下也有食肆和小店 逛到熱也可以去食點東西
